title: Sunshine, humidity3pm
body: We can notice that when we take humidity at 3 PM into account and sunshine, we see that if humidity above 66.67 percent and sunshine is below 4.77 hours, there is a 67.8 percent of chance that rain will happen tomorrow.

title: Sunshine
body:
We can notice that sunshine has the highest purity rating. If sunshine is less than 4.77 hours there is a maximum chance of rain happening the following day. 23 % of total instances have sunshine b/w 0-4.77 hours with 50% approx that it will rain tomorrow.

We also notice that we have higher incorrect predictions for bin one and 2 as compared to the third bin.

title: Sunshine, humidity 3pm, wind gust speed
body: When we add wind gust speed to the sunshine and humidity at 3 pm features we notice that higher wind gust speed increases the chance of rainfall for tomorrow, and the percentage of that increases with an increase in the percentage of humidity with the highest probability of rainfall for sunshine hours less than 4.77 hours.
